data.title: Nobel Physicists and Their Discoveries
data.meta_description: Nobel Physicists and Their Discoveries - Free ebook download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read book online for free. This document provides an introduction and overview of the Nobel Prize in Physics. It discusses how the prize is awarded annually by the Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences for outstanding contributions to physics. Each recipient receives a medal, diploma and monetary award. The document then lists every Nobel Laureate in Physics from 1901 to the present, with their country of origin and the page number where more information can be found in the referenced book. It concludes by praising the author for their comprehensive compilation of information on Nobel Prize winning physicists.
